\f0\fs72 \cf2 FemtoduinoBLE - Get started with Bluetooth 4.0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl440\sa400

\f1\fs32 \cf2 The FemtoduinoBLE sports the same power and pin count as the Arduino Leonardo, in a smaller package and with on-board BLE.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa200

\f2\fs28 \cf2 Unlike other solutions, the FemtoduinoBLE uses BlueGiga's BLE113 module which already meets radio frequency requirements in multiple countries. Additionally, the on-board USB is fully integrated into the ATMEGA32u4, so your FemtoduinoBLE can also be used to emulate a Keyboard or Mouse!\
A key benefit to using a BlueGiga module instead of a custom Bluetooth 4.0 design is ease of use. The BLE113 module can be interfaced via the BGLib Arduino library, so you can take more time dreaming up the next big idea, instead of fighting hardware troubles.\
